author: Christopher S. Stewart
title: Jeb Bush Disclosure on His Campaign ‘Bundlers’ Spurs Criticism
text:
Jeb Bush on Thursday is expected to become the first Republican presidential candidate to release the names of supporters who are bundling campaign contributions—although with a twist.
Mr. Bush is defining bundlers as donors who have raised at least $17,600, according to people familiar with the disclosure plan, a much lower threshold than used by past presidential campaigns and by Democratic rival Hillary Clinton, who is...
